📣 Attention Minecraft players!

Wayne MOST is launching a Minecraft server for students in Wayne County to interact and build in a safe environment. The server will start with students in sixth through 12th grades, but students of all ages can sign up and the server will be expanded based on interest. Scheduled sessions will be monitored for inappropriate language and behavior.

To register, visit bit.ly/mostminecraft.

post_text:
To provide feedback on your feelings on school reopening, please complete the initial questions in this survey.
https://www.surveygizmo.com/s3/5657688/Parent-Voice-Survey-2020

The initial feedback on school reopening will take less than two minutes, and the survey as a whole will take less than five minutes. Your survey will help us gather insight and understanding first on your perspective on reopening school and then on the impact of virtual learning over the past few months.

While guidance from NYS and directives from our own local Public Health Department are governing forces in our decision making, we would like to make sure that we are as inclusive and as sensitive as we can be to the needs of the families we serve.

Data is being collected by Evalumetrics Research in partnership with Finger Lakes Community Schools and any questions may be directed to jroscup@flxcommunityschools.org; each district will receive a copy of their own data. Each district will also receive a copy of the county data for comparison.

post_text: MEAL DELIVERY PROGRAM UPDATE: Beginning May 11th, breakfast and lunch will be delivered directly to all students in the district on Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays, from 9 am – 11 am. There will no longer be an option to pick up meals at the high school. Every student will have meals for Monday and Tuesday delivered each Monday. Meals for Wednesday and Thursday will be delivered on Wednesday, and Friday’s breakfast and lunch will be delivered each Friday. All students in the district are automatically enrolled in this delivery program and will have meals delivered directly to their homes. There is no action required to participate in the delivery program. If you would like to opt-out of meal delivery for your child, please contact us by emailing meals@nrwcs.org or calling (315) 594-5510.

post_text: The 2020 Census counts every person living in our communities and affects the funding our communities receive for public services for the next 10 years. This year, you can fill out your census form online by going to www.2020census.gov, clicking on “respond now” then “start now”. If you have an invite code from the form you received in the mail, enter it there. If not, click on “If you do not have your census ID click here.” The process will take 10 minutes or less and will make sure our communities receive our share of federal funding.

post_text: FEEDING SITE INFO: The district has established an emergency feeding site for students in grades PreK-12. The distribution site will be located at the North Rose-Wolcott High School, located at 11631 Salter-Colvin Road, Wolcott, NY and will operate from 10:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. Monday – Friday, beginning Tuesday, March 17th. A pre-packaged, take-out breakfast and lunch will be provided for North Rose-Wolcott Central School District students. Our boys varsity volleyball team had a celebratory dinner and was honored at last night's board meeting for receiving the Gary Adler Sportsmanship award. After each match this season, Section V officials graded each team's players, coaches, and fans based on their behavior at the match.

At the end of the season, sportsmanship scores were averaged to determine a winner, and NRW received the highest score in Section V. Congratulations to our volleyball team and fans!

post_text:
We would like to give a special shout out to an extremely talented student.

AnnaMae, a senior at NRW High School, was selected for the NYSSMA Conference All-State Mixed Chorus earlier this year. She leaves this afternoon and will rehearse all weekend before performing in the NYSSMA Conference All-State Festival on Sunday at Eastman.

This is a huge honor for AnnaMae as she was selected from all students throughout New York State. She is the first NRW student to receive Conference All-State honors since 2014.

Please join us in congratulating AnnaMae for this outstanding achievement!
